<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-503-019  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 503 019.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Oct 8 1990 n321 p14(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PCS debated: FCC gets industry remarks. (personal communicationsservices) (Federal Communications Commission) (includes relatedarticle on 'PCS: smart cells, call anywhere')</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission hears testimony fromcellular industry experts and professional associations pertainingto the regulation of personal communications services.andP;  PCS isconsidered a natural extension of cellular mobile radiotechnology, and the FCC seeks to develop a position on thedevelopment of such services by the cellular industry.andP;  Amongother factors, the FCC sought comments on the amount of spectrumnecessary to develop PCS technology, which technology types shouldbe accorded developmental priority, what technical standardsshould be applied and the extent to which such services should beregulated.andP;  The FCC proposal to exclude both telephone companiesand holders of cellular licenses from PCS provision was criticizedthose firms.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Cellular RadioIndustry AnalysisMobile Radio SystemsCommunications ApplicationsUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionTrade and Professional AssociationsLobbying.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>